<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Inline replaced elements with intrinsic ratios and height and width are auto</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="HTMLonly invalid" />
        <meta name="assert" content="If 'height' and 'width' both have computed values of 'auto' and the element also has an intrinsic width, then that intrinsic width is the used value of 'width'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                width: 300px;
                height: 20px;
                background-color: green;
                border: solid 1px black;
            }
            #d2
            {
                width: 50%;
            }
            iframe
            {
                height: auto;
                width: auto;
                border: solid 1px black;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the green box has the same width as the box above it.</p>
        <iframe></iframe>
        <div id="d1"></div>
        <div id="d2"></div>
    </body>
</html>